{"metadata":{"title":"StaticRWLock","symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib12StaticRWLockC","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLock"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLock"}],"roleHeading":"Class"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLock"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Take a look at the following example:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["  GStaticRWLock rwlock = G_STATIC_RW_LOCK_INIT;","  GPtrArray *array;","","  gpointer","  my_array_get (guint index)","  {","    gpointer retval = NULL;","","    if (!array)","      return NULL;","","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock (&rwlock);","    if (index < array->len)","      retval = g_ptr_array_index (array, index);","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock (&rwlock);","","    return retval;","  }","","  void","  my_array_set (guint index, gpointer data)","  {","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_lock (&rwlock);","","    if (!array)","      array = g_ptr_array_new ();","","    if (index >= array->len)","      g_ptr_array_set_size (array, index + 1);","    g_ptr_array_index (array, index) = data;","","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock (&rwlock);","  }"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows an array which can be accessed by many readers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_get()"},{"type":"text","text":" function) simultaneously, whereas the writers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_set()"},{"type":"text","text":" function) will only be allowed once at a time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and only if no readers currently access the array. This is because"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the potentially dangerous resizing of the array. Using these","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"functions is fully multi-thread safe now.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Most of the time, writers should have precedence over readers. That","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"means, for this implementation, that as soon as a writer wants to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lock the data, no other reader is allowed to lock the data, whereas,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of course, the readers that already have locked the data are allowed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to finish their operation. As soon as the last reader unlocks the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"data, the writer will lock it."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even though [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] is not opaque, it should only be used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the following functions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the "},{"code":"g_static_rw_lock_*","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" functions can be used even if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Thread.init"},{"type":"text","text":"] has not been called. Then they do nothing, apart"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_*_trylock"},{"text":", which does nothing but returning true.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A read-write lock has a higher overhead than a mutex. For example, both","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StaticRWLock.reader_lock"},{"text":"] and [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StaticRWLock.reader_unlock"},{"text":"] have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to lock and unlock a [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"], so it takes at least twice the time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to lock and unlock a [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] that it does to lock and unlock a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"text":"]. So only data structures that are accessed by multiple","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"readers, and which keep the lock for a considerable time justify a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"]. The above example most probably would fare better with a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticRWLock"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticRWLock"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticRWLock"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlock"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-33hto","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-3kcsg","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-3zz8s","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-5u2m3","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-8mhsi","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(raw:)-3slj2","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(raw:)-7ng5h","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib